reviews.review_text: NIce one! One of the best!
so HEADY look at the set nuff said such sick quality too

Great show This is a practically perfect show with some incredible highlights.  I put the Estimated in the top few ever... seriously.  Great ChinaRider, Wharf Rat, Bird Song, too.  
At the time, I thought this was the best of the 3 shows of this stellar run, and I still do.  
Great soundboard, too.
I'll never forget this one! It was my first show. I was 12 and got the tickets from my teacher! Don't worry, that's all I got from him :)
Post-Show Raves in the UPenn Quad The post-show parties were all night and epic. Great run. Just as good as '83 and '90.

Trippy 84 Dead The Baby Blue is haunting - one of the best ever, all weird Mydland effects and Junky Jerry yearning. Check out the Wharf Rat too - Garcia buries several extended solos during an 11+ minute epic.

To: 31590 and Who Might Listen I Figure That's Probably Your Birth Date.Following The Band For Years Jerry's Drug Use Was Well Known But As We Crossed From '83 To '84 It Was No Longer Deniable That He Was Using.At The Point Of This Show And Especially This Run Of Philly Civic Shows He Was Still Getting The Exploratory Runs In His Playing Though His Vocals And Attention Were Waning.Those Who Were Close In Knew How Long And What But Most Were Oblivious Along For The Party And The Ride.(One In 10,000 Come For The Show It Is Said).Regardless Remember That Addiction Is A Sickness That Has Many Victims,Some Gone Some Still Here And Still Hurting.My Own Family Has Been Touched By The Recent Opiate Epidemic.I Have Lost Cousins And Still See Family Members Struggling On A Daily Basis To Stay Clean And Reclaim Thier Previous Lives. Know That Your Words In There Context Are Cruel.I Hope You And Yours Stay Clear Of This Disease No Matter What The Substance Or Habit It Might Manifest As. All I Want To Know Is Are You Kind.(Robert Wasn't Writing About An Indica Breed).And Remember Jerry's Listening. Forever Grateful

Killer 1984 show! I'd take this over anything after 1992-93. Jerry was really still rocking it, especially in early/mid 84, This show proves it imo. Later 84 can be more hit or miss but this spring tour was killer. Thank you Mr Garcia.  PS; I liked Jerry's look in 84, he was like a hippie redneck looks wise Lol. He didn't move a lot on stage BUT listen to the music play!!

My first show What a phenomenal recording of the show that quite literally changed my life.  The second set was almost too overwhelming for @n unaccompanied 13 year old kid, after Chinacat->Rider melted my mind, I wasn’t prepared for the bone-deep weirdness of a well-played Estimated,and the drugs were really kicking in…. It wasn’t until “The Wheel” that I had a chance to gather myself but the calm lasted only until The thunder don’t get you  and up up up from the moment I got up to fly away through every 13 year old skeletons in the closet fan’s secret wish and that’s for a set closing Sugar Mags and sure enough, but who called the sweet Baby Blue encore?  Wow, I thought I’d overhyped this show in my memory given its significance but, no, it’s actually a rocked out very well played show. No wonder they became habit forming so quick.
